<item>
            <title>[TIKA-1024] An MP3 with an UTF-16 ID3 tag containing only the BOM should produce empty string value for that tag</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-1024</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This seems to be a difference between JVMs: on IBM&apos;s JVM I incorrectly see the BOM as the value of the tag, while on Oracle&apos;s JVM I correctly get the empty string.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure if this is a bug in IBM&apos;s JVM ... the javadocs are not totally clear how a UTF-16 string containing only the BOM should be decoded by new String(...) ... to fix this I think we should just detect this case and short-circuit empty string return.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
